Hi, my name is Hing Huynh. I am currently 25 year olds and am currently working to pursue a career in software development. I previously studied economics and accounting while I was in college at UCLA. Since college I've pursued various careers as a realtor, loan officer, business broker, and a day trader. It really wasn't until after college that I started dabbling in things that I started find what I had the vague interest in. I'm hoping that as I spend more time learning to program that it will become more and more passionate about it.

A little about myself. I love to read. I love to read non-fiction books related to business,self-development, and health and wellness, but also recently developed a recent addiction to sci-fi. The most recent books that I've read are "Atlantis Gene" and "Atlantis Plague." This is a wonderful sci-fi series written by A.G. Riddle. A.G. Riddle beautifully intertwines real historical data with some fiction to create a thrilling series about fight between human extinction and evolution. I highly recommend if you love sci-fi to check these books out.
